DA in Ekurhuleni replaces its Caucus leadership 15 September 2020 The Democratic Alliance (DA) notes that the DA in Ekurhuleni will replace its Caucus Leader and Chairperson at its next Caucus meeting. This followed motions of no confidence in the incumbents, Councillors de Lange and Haggard. A new leadership will be elected on 28 September 2020 to continue our programme of exposing poor service delivery, corruption and maladministration in the ANC-led City of Ekurhuleni. The DA is confident that the Caucus will elect new leadership who will take the team forward to continue to offer hope for the future of the country in the upcoming elections.eval(ez_write_tag([[580,400],'politicsweb_co_za-medrectangle-3','ezslot_4',113,'0','0'])); In all we do, the residents and the quality service delivery are our first priority. Issued by Solly Msimanga, DA Gauteng Interim Leader, 15 September 2020